  "text": "Successfully removed Cairo dependency from the sprite generator. The project now works with pure Python dependencies and generates SVG-only output. This is actually better for sprite sheets since SVG is scalable and doesn't require system libraries. The generator runs cleanly and creates a 20x20 grid of procedurally generated door agents with different eyes, mouths, colors, and body shapes. All assets are now in place and the workflow is streamlined.",
  "sections": [
    "Project Notes"
  ],
